  <source>Office of Rare Diseases (ORD)</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      OBJECTIVES:

      Determine the relationship between serum calcium concentrations and parathyroid hormone
      secretion in patients with pseudohypoparathyroidism.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      PROTOCOL OUTLINE:

      Patients are tested for parathyroid hormone response following sequential graded intravenous
      infusions of sodium citrate and calcium gluconate. Assays include ionized calcium and intact
      parathyroid hormone.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
